# Package Structure

Root package: `com.chriswininger`

## Entry point

`com.chriswininger.cli.EntryCommand` ‚Äî the `@TopCommand` entry point.
New subcommands are added to its `subcommands` array.

## Command packages under `cli/commands/`

Each command lives in its own package under `com.chriswininger.cli.commands`:

```
com.chriswininger.cli.commands.<name>/
  ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ <Name>Command.java          # @Command implementing Runnable
  ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ dto/                         # Domain-specific DTOs (records)
  ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ services/                    # Business logic services
```

When adding a new command, create a new package following this pattern and register
it in `EntryCommand`'s `subcommands` array.

## Generated API client (`com.chriswininger.client`)

A typed HTTP client is auto-generated from `../openapi-specs/openapi.json`
(produced by `document-ingestion-api`) at build time via the OpenAPI Generator
Gradle plugin. The output lives in `build/generated/openapi/` and is **not**
checked into source.

- `com.chriswininger.client` ‚Äî `ApiClient`, configuration, JSON helpers
- `com.chriswininger.client.api` ‚Äî one API class per REST resource
- `com.chriswininger.client.model` ‚Äî DTOs matching the API's schemas

**Do not edit generated code.** To change the client, either:
1. Update the endpoint in `document-ingestion-api`, rebuild it (which
   regenerates the spec), then rebuild this project.
2. Adjust generator settings in `build.gradle.kts` under `openApiGenerate`.

## Placement guide

| You're adding‚Ä¶ | Put it in‚Ä¶ |
|----------------|-----------|
| New subcommand | `cli/commands/<name>/<Name>Command.java` + register in `EntryCommand` |
| New DTO for a command | `cli/commands/<name>/dto/` |
| New business service | `cli/commands/<name>/services/` |
| Shared utility across commands | `cli/util/` |
| Shared service across commands | `cli/services/` |
| API client usage | Import from `com.chriswininger.client.api` ‚Äî never hand-write HTTP calls |
